11. Section 392.25 is revised to read as follows: 



392.25

Emergency signals; dangerous cargoes. 



No driver shall use or permit the use of any flame-producing emergency signal for protecting any motor vehicle transporting
Division 1.1, Division 1.2, or Division 1.3 explosives; any cargo tank motor vehicle used for the transportation
of any Class 3 or Division 2.1, whether loaded or empty; or any motor vehicle using compressed gas as a motor fuel. In
lieu thereof, emergency reflective triangles, red electric lanterns, or red emergency reflectors shall be used,
the placement of which shall be in the same manner as prescribed in 392.22(b). 



PART 397_[AMENDED] 



